{
  "texts": [
    "Reaching a certain level of explainability in AI models is possible by either developing models that are inherently more interpretable -but sometimes have less predictive power-or by using post-hoc XAI techniques to generate explanations after predictions have been made with a black-box model.",
    "Even though seemingly good explanations for a model's decision can be generated by the use of a post-hoc XAI method, and consequently the model and its decisions are qualified as transparent, research on the uniformity of these explanations is rather scarce.",
    "Many different post-hoc XAI methods exist and each method can generate different explanations for the same predicted outcome.",
    "Ergo, different stakeholders might be more interested in the explanations of one specific XAI method over another one.",
    "This raises the question of whether the transparency objective of XAI is achieved."
  ]
}